OL,3,CSir Chris Hoy breaks leg in 'worst
OL,4,Ccrash he ever had'
OL,6,FIn an interview with Sky Sports, the
OL,7,F49-year-old said: "I've smashed my leg
OL,8,Fup on the mountain bike, that's the
OL,9,Fworst thing that's happened recently.
OL,10,FYou just don't bounce like you do when
OL,11,Fyou're younger. It was a big one, but
OL,12,FI'm better now. I'm still on crutches,
OL,13,Fhobbling about.
OL,15,F"Worse things happen. I've been riding
OL,16,Fbikes for 43 years and it's the worst
OL,17,Fcrash I've ever hard. I'm pretty lucky
OL,18,Fthat's the worst one I've had in all
OL,19,Fthose years of riding."
