OL,3,CSir Chris Hoy breaks leg in 'worst
OL,4,Ccrash he ever had'
OL,6,FHoy announced in February 2024 that he
OL,7,Fwas undergoing treatment for prostate
OL,8,Fcancer, and in October that year, he
OL,9,Frevealed doctors had given him between
OL,10,Ftwo and four years to live.
OL,12,FThe 49-year-old is Britain's second
OL,13,Fmost decorated Olympian behind his
OL,14,Fformer team-mate Sir Jason Kenny.
